website_summaries.verdict: A rich, flavorful chicken puree without artificial ingredients. This thick blend of meaty mush works well for picky, injured, or elderly cats.
pros: A high-moisture tube of real pureed chicken
Chicken is the second ingredient, after water

customer_reviews.title: Good quality, healthy treats that my cats go crazy for!
customer_reviews.text: Oh, yes, these hit the spot with my three fur monsters! I have two ways of feeding these treats: I break the pieces into smaller pieces and sprinkle them over their regular food. Sometimes, I give them as treats. The cats' reaction to my breaking out the chicken treats is something to behold: they come running from whatever corner/floor of the house (they can hear me opening these treat from miles away!) and perform a zoomie happy-dance upon seeing me handing out the treats!
customer_reviews.author: Claudia Grinnell

customer_reviews.title: Bought for our dog
customer_reviews.text: These are the export version of a treat we buy in Japan for our picky dog who likes chicken more than dogfood . This company also makes a treat for dogs, but it's more expensive for basically the same thing as the cat treat. Compared to the Fancy Feast version sold for 1.99 in my local pet shop, these are a bargain.
customer_reviews.author: Mrs. 髙﨑

customer_reviews.title: Good choice for a cat with no teeth
customer_reviews.text: We have a cat who had to have all of his teeth pulled because of an infection he had from being a stray. These seem to be perfect for him - they’re slightly moist so they don’t stick to his mouth. And they are nice and soft which are perfect for a kitty with no teeth. We’ve also tried the ones from Fancy Feast but these seem to be a bit softer.

customer_reviews.title: Even the finickiest
customer_reviews.text: My Frenchy Poo Who absolutely Adores these! She doesn't like any other cat treat, just these. She sits in the kitchen and I ask her, "Do you want a chicken snack?" Immediately she licks her lips and makes the sound that a cat would normally make if they see a bird at the window. (that weird, "aa-aa-aa-aa" sound). She eats the entire fillet. It's pretty impressive for a cat treat; actual fillet that smells like, well, people food.
